## User pool configuration

### Step 1: Custom attributes

#### Step 1.1: Add custom attributes

User pool: GardenWorld \> Sign-up experience \> Add custom attributes  
![][image17]  
![][image18]

#### Step 1.2 Edit custom attribute read and write permissions

User pool: GardenWorld \> App integration \> App client: iDempiere Web Client \> Attribute read and write permissions \> Edit

Edit attribute read and write permissions for the custom attributes created above  
![][image19]

### Step 2: Create user

User pool: GardenWorld \> Users \> Create user

*Notes:*   
*User name \= iDempiere user (AD\_User.Name)*  
*Email address \= iDempiere user (AD\_User.EMail)*  
*User has to login for the first time using the temporary password to change new password*  
![][image20]  
![][image21]

### Step 3: Configure the custom attributes for user

User pool: GardenWorld \> Users \> User: GardenAdmin \> User attributes \> Edit

Add attribute for the custom attribute created above  
![][image22]  
![][image23]

### Step 4: Create group

User pool: GardenWorld \> Groups \> Create group

*Note: Group name \= iDempiere role (AD\_Role.Name) without space*  
![][image24]

### Step 5: Add user to group

User pool: GardenWorld \> Groups \> Group: GardenWorldAdmin \> Add user to group  
![][image25]

### Step 6: Add Lambda trigger

User pool: GardenWorld \> User pool properties \> Lambda triggers \> Add Lambda trigger

*Note: Refer to the Step 7 to Create Lambda function. After that, select the Lambda function created in Step 7 as the Lambda function \> Assign Lambda function.*  
![][image26]  
![][image27]

### Step 7: Create Lambda function

#### Step 7.1: Create function

User pool: GardenWorld \> User pool properties \> Lambda triggers \> Add Lambda trigger \> Lambda function \> Create Lambda function

Lambda \> Functions \> Create function  
![][image28]

#### Step 7.2: Enter the Code

Lambda \> Functions \> Function name: PreTokenGeneration \> Code \> Code souce \> index.mjs  
![][image29]

    export const handler \= async (event) \=\> {  
      console.log("Received event: ", JSON.stringify(event, null, 2));  
          
        // Example: Extract custom attributes from the userAttributes field  
        const userAttributes \= event.request.userAttributes;
    
        // Check if user attributes contain the custom claims we want to add  
        const organization \= userAttributes\["custom:X-ID-Organization"\];  
        const role \= userAttributes\["custom:X-ID-Role"\];  
        const warehouse \= userAttributes\["custom:X-ID-Warehouse"\];  
        const language \= userAttributes\["custom:X-ID-Language"\];  
          
        // Modify the token by adding custom claims to the payload  
        event.response \= {  
            claimsOverrideDetails: {  
                claimsToAddOrOverride: {  
                    "X-ID-Organization": organization,  
                    "X-ID-Role": role,  
                    "X-ID-Warehouse": warehouse,  
                    "X-ID-Language": language  
                }  
            }  
        };
    
        console.log("Modified token claims: ", event.response.claimsOverrideDetails);  
    console.log("Modified event: ", JSON.stringify(event, null, 2));  
        return event;  // Return the modified event  
    };

### Step 8: Get region, User pool ID, Client ID and Client secret 

#### Step 8.1: Copy User pool ID

User pool: GardenWorld \> App integration

Copy the User pool ID and region

Note: You can find the region info from the Token signing key URL. Token signing key URL format \- [https://cognito-idp.\[region\].amazonaws.com/\[userPoolId\]/.well-known/jwks.json](https://cognito-idp.[region].amazonaws.com/[userPoolId]/.well-known/jwks.json)    
![][image34]

#### Step 8.2: Copy Client ID and Client secret

User pool: GardenWorld \> App integration \> App client: iDempiere Web Client

Copy the Client ID and Client secret  
![][image35]

## Step 9: Configure the Rest OpenID Connect Service

iDempiere Web Client \> Tenant: GardenWorld \> Rest OpenID Connect Service

Authority URL format \- [https://cognito-idp.\[region\].amazonaws.com/\[userPoolId](https://cognito-idp.[region].amazonaws.com/[userPoolId)\]  
Audience \- User pool: GardenWorld \> App integration \> App client: iDempiere Web Client \> Client ID  
![][image36]

## Step 10: Generate Secret Hash

* Combine the User name and Client ID into a single string  
* Hash the combined string using the HMAC-SHA256 algorithm and the client secret as the key  
* Base64 encode the resulting hash

## Step 11: Testing using Postman

* Import amazon-cognito-oidc-test.postman\_collection.json and environment-http---localhost-8080.postman\_environment.json to Postman  
* Set variable value  
  * cognitoRegion \- Get region value from Step 8.1  
  * cognitoUsername \- User name of User pool: GardenWorld \> Users \> User: GardenAdmin  
  * cognitoPassword \- Password of User pool: GardenWorld \> Users \> User: GardenAdmin  
  * cognitoSecretHash \- Get the generated secret hash from Step 10  
  * cognitoClientId \- Get Client ID value from Step 8.1
